  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Winterization Assistance to the Most Vulnerable Affected and Displaced Populations in Afghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan is facing critical humanitarian needs, with the winter season posing particular risks for families unable to adequately prepare for severe weather conditions. In responding to these needs, IOM will provide critical winterization support to displaced and otherwise vulnerable families through the distribution of Cash-for-Winterization (heater/fuel) to 8,000 families; Provision of complementary non-food item (NFI) assistance to 6,500 families (blanket and warm clothing); and Distribution of Cash-for-Shelter Repair/upgrade to 840 families. A total of 61,880 individuals (average 7 persons per family) will be directly targeted for assistance. Each of the three interventions: Cash-for-shelter, Cash-for-winterization and complementary NFI support will have different beneficiaries selected for each intervention. The beneficiaries selection will be done through joint need assessments (using winterization needs assessment tool for winterization assistance and shelter assessment tool for shelter repair/upgrade) together with other humanitarian partners in the provinces. This will be undertaken in coordination with relevant operational partners in the targeted provinces including De Facto authorities at Afghanistan National Disaster Management Authority (ANDMA) HQ and provinces, Ministry of Refugee and Repatriation (MoRR) and Directorate of Refugees and Repatriation (DoRRs). IOM will also closely coordinate the assessment and distribution with UNHCR, as both agencies have CERF funding for complementary activities.</narrative>
  </description>
